Diagnosis.
This species can be distinguished from other congeners by 1) male palpal ventral surface distinctly elevated, forming a hump (
Fig. 2E
); 2) embolus lacking any modifications (
Fig. 2F
); 3) copulatory ducts of the female genitalia are extremely wide (
Dankittipakul & Singtripop 2014: 22, figs 12, 19
).
